##Many places in Hubei outside Wuhan are in dire need of medical supplies: Masks are in short supply and can not be bought at all

The protective materials available at the First People's Hospital in Xianning can only last one day, the protective clothing of the Chinese Medicine Hospital in Xiangyang is out, N95 masks need to be disinfected and reused, and the rubber gloves at the Hanchuan People's Hospital are running out.

2,306 words, about 5 minutes to read

On January 26, several hospitals from various parts of Hubei Province confirmed to the Beijing News that medical protective materials were in urgent need. They have issued a donation announcement to the community.

As of 2400 hours on January 25,1,052 confirmed cases of COVID-19 pneumonia had been reported in the province, including 618 in Wuhan, 122 in Huanggang, 55 in Xiaogan and 43 in Xianning, according to the Provincial Health Commission.

Besides Wuhan, the epidemic prevention situation of other cities and states in Hubei Province has been paid more and more attention.

The reporter from the Hsinking newspaper learned that the protective materials in hospitals in Xiaogan, Xianning, Ensch, Xiangyang and other places are all in urgent need. The protective materials available in the First People's Hospital of Xianning can only last for one day, and the protective clothing in the Chinese Medicine Hospital of Xiangyang has been exhausted, the N95 mask needs to be disinfected and reused, and the rubber gloves of the Hanchuan People's Hospital are about to be used up.

━━━━━

Xiaogan: Face Mask and face mask are in short supply

Xiaogan City Center hospital staff told the Beijing News that the hospital is most in need of protective clothing, N95 masks, a daily demand of 300 pieces. On the night of Jan. 24, the hospital issued a donation notice. On Jan. 26, it received a small number of protective clothing, barely enough to last four or five days, but still no N95 masks and face masks, and the masks were in very small stock.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Donation announcement of Xiaogan Central Hospital. Photo provided by interviewees

Xiaogan First People's hospital staff also said that the shortage of masks, the initial demand is 10,000, after the demand will increase, depending on the number of patients admitted.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Announcement of donation of Xiaogan First People's Hospital. Photo courtesy of the respondents

Xianning First People's Hospital: Need 5,000 N95 masks

Staff at Xianning Central Hospital said they currently require 5,000 N95 masks and 1,000 to 2,000 protective masks, protective clothing and the number of half a month to maintain: "A few days ago someone has sent us SF express, but I do not know why, have not received. At present, our medical staff is relatively safe, but people are very tired. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Donation notice of Xianning Central Hospital. Photo by respondents

According to an emergency letter with official seals provided by the staff of Xianning's First People's hospital to a Beijing News reporter, the protective materials available at the hospital can only last for one day, and many medical workers do not protect themselves, donations from all walks of life are urgently needed. Staff at the hospital told the Beijing News that some of the most needed masks had already been donated, but they were still stuck on the road.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Demand Note for emergency assistance and donations from the First People's Hospital in Xianning. Photo courtesy of the respondents

"On a 15-day basis, twenty-seven thousand N95 masks, twenty-seven thousand surgical masks and twenty-seven thousand disposable surgical masks, fourteen thousand protective clothing, goggles, protective masks, latex gloves, disinfectant, and 1,000 COVID-19. The daily consumption is very high, so there is a serious emergency. But now it's very difficult for individuals to mail in, and it needs a connection between a factory and a courier company,"said the official.

ENSCH: Some of the hospital's protective equipment will last only a few days

The staff of the Lichuan People's Hospital in Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture said that when the donation announcement was made, the protective materials could only last for three or five days. At present, donations from some caring people have been received one after another, mask, goggles, protective masks and other requirements are still about 10,000. "At present, the health care workers are in good condition and there are no cases of cross-infection. "

Hefeng County is the only county-level city in Hubei Province that does not have high-speed access. A hospital official at Hefeng County's Central Hospital told the Beijing News that medical supplies can only last a few days and that there is a shortage of 10,000 masks and protective clothing.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Donation notice for Hefeng County Central Hospital. Photo provided by respondents

Xiangyang Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine: Disinfection and Reuse of surgical masks

Huangshi, Xiangyang and Xianning were the first confirmed cases reported in the notification issued by the Hubei Provincial Health Commission. Contacted by the HSINKING newspaper, hospitals in Xiangyang said they had made donations to the community because of the large number of people returning home from Wuhan and the shortage of medical supplies.

"At the time of the announcement, there was nothing left in the protective clothing. We are now wearing hospital isolation clothing that has been repeatedly disinfected and an additional layer of disposable surgical clothes, " a staff member at the Xiangyang Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine told the Beijing News, "At noon today, only 30 pairs of N95 masks were left. They had to be sterilized and reused. "

The above-mentioned staff said that at present, medical and nursing staff are also working overtime, and the hospital has brewed some traditional Chinese medicine, "since the N95 mask consumption is between 100 and 150 per day, 80 sets of protective clothing per day, if the number of a week, hope to donate 200 protective clothing, we give first-line direct contact with the case, others we use ordinary, so that the community can also donate to other places in need of supplies for use. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Donation notice for Xiangyang Chinese Medicine Hospital. Photo provided by interviewees

Staff at another hospital, Xiangyang Central Hospital, said they hoped to get help from the community and would donate as much as they could at present, most in need of N95 masks and protective clothing.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Donation notice for Xiangyang Central Hospital. Photo provided by respondents

Hanchuan: N95 masks and gloves in short supply

A doctor at the Hanchuan People's Hospital told the Beijing News that there is a serious shortage of materials in the hospital. There is no N95 mask left. The first-line medical staff can only wear two layers of medical surgical masks to continue their work. He said health care workers had been suspended, more than 1,600 people were on duty and more than 2,000 masks were consumed each day, supplies are running out: "We are out of N95 masks in Hanchuan. There is no place to buy them. What we lack most is these masks. "

The doctor said rubber gloves were also being used quickly at the hospital, which is running out of stock: "medical staff need to examine patients in complete isolation, " he said, at present these materials are very difficult to buy in the city, "we went directly to the medical equipment factory, but the effect is not ideal. "

The doctor said the hospital had no choice but to seek help from the community, spread out through volunteers to raise money, or through official charities.

In addition, the doctor said that although the donation of goggles to the community, but the need to remind donors, not all goggles meet the requirements of medical protection. "You need something with a rubber band around the rim of the eye that keeps the eye safely isolated from the outside world so bacteria can not get in from the eye. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Material demand table of Hanchuan People's Hospital

The Second People's Hospital in Hanchuan is facing the same problem.

"Masks are the least available, " a doctor told the Beijing News, adding that doctors and nurses are taking extra care to minimize the frequency of replacement, but masks are still not enough. "things like masks, rubber gloves and protective clothing, many of which are disposable, lose their effectiveness when used repeatedly. "

The doctor said the hospital is also looking for their own way, but the effect is not good: "Out of stock is too serious, and manufacturers ask, they can not say when exactly can be available. "

HSINKING newspaper reporter, Wang Yuqian, editor Zhang Jingya, proofread by Guo Chen, Wang Xin
